{"id": 4621, "title": "Ticket #4621: Help CMS use a very small condor_shadow_s", "description": "<blockquote>\nCMS has started to use the condor_shadow_s on its pools.  In 8.3.1, this shrinks the per-shadow RAM usage to 640kb.  We can do better:\n<ul>\n<li>krb5 is not used and (looking at the smaps, could be a big consumer of RAM).\n</li><li>The 32-bit shadow_s would be much smaller than the 64-bit one.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>So, here's an idea:\n</p><ul>\n<li>Remove KRB5 linkage from condor_shadow_s daemon.  If you need to use KRB5, then you're stuck with condor_shadow.\n</li><li>Move condor_master_s from condor-static-shadow to the base condor\u00a0RPM.\n<ul>\n<li>I do not believe we can mix the 32-bit condor_master with the 64-bit condor_procd without further work.  Binary datastructs (such as struct <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ProcFamilyUsage\" title=\"Proc Family Usage\">ProcFamilyUsage</a></span>, which differs in size between the 32-bit and 64-bit build) are in the procd protocol and written directly across the Unix socket.\n</li></ul>\n</li><li>Do not ship the 64-bit condor-static-shadow RPM.\n</li><li>Place the 32-bit condor-static-shadow RPM in the 64-bit release repo.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>This would allow us to cleanly install the 32-bit static via puppet using RPMs.  All the other mechanisms so far require hackery of the RPM DB or installing from tarballs.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-20 14:47</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8236a56c12554cd42a228fed512639e487b9bd8d\">[44671]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4621\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4621'); return false;\" title=\"Help CMS use a very small condor_shadow_s\">#4621</a></span>) Documentation and Version History  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-16 11:19</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/f09c13f18446c6658d0a88509868c9774e474aee\">[44645]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4621\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4621'); return false;\" title=\"Help CMS use a very small condor_shadow_s\">#4621</a></span>) Get build id into version string  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-15 21:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c00c30048a091a1f091df54ba7ee1f017252d759\">[44637]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4621\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4621'); return false;\" title=\"Help CMS use a very small condor_shadow_s\">#4621</a></span>) Don't install BOSCO config files by default  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-15 21:42</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/60eab4598bdbaee30a28af19b8a76febbec24337\">[44636]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4621\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and